YouTube mainly runs on Google’s own cloud ecosystem, not on third-party clouds.

1. Client Layer

Web App / Mobile App → Used to provide user interface for watching, uploading and interacting with videos → Used when applications must support multi-device access.

HTML5 Video Player → Used to stream videos directly in browser without plugins → Used when cross-platform video playback is required.

Google Front End (GFE) → Entry point server that receives user requests → Used when global applications need a secure edge entry layer.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. DNS + Routing Layer

Google DNS → Converts youtube.com into IP address → Used when applications need domain name resolution.

Anycast Routing → Routes users to nearest data center → Used when latency must be minimized globally.

Edge POP Servers → First contact servers near users → Used when reducing response delay is critical.
